    <etym xml:lang="ru">Очевидно, из %iа%i + *%ipuz-yn%i, где в основе *%ipuz%i- легко опознать
            <mentioned xml:lang="ine"
            ><lang/><w>*pu</w><gloss><q>вздувать(ся)</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ine"><w/><gloss><q>пучить(ся)</q></gloss></mentioned>, и пр., с наращенным
        -%ig%i (→ %iz%i); ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pūga-</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w>puñja-</w><gloss><q>масса</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
            xml:lang="ru"><lang/><w>пузо</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"
            ><w>пузырь</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πυγή</w></mentioned> и
        пр. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II 79—81</biblScope></bibl>). То, что
        %iр%i не перешел в %if(v)%i, вопреки звуковому закону, следует объяснить характерной
        „выразительностью“ губных %ip%i, %ib%i для понятий „вздувания“, „вспучивания“, по сравнению
        со спирантами. Обращает на себя внимание одинаковая огласовка в иронском и дигорском: %iu%i
        | %iu%i, вместо ожидаемого %iy%i | %iu%i или %iu%i | %iо%i.%r1%r К осетинскому примыкает,
        возможно, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>buzva</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                ><w>abuzva</w><gloss><q>нахохлиться</q></gloss></mentioned>, .</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Clearly derived from %ia%i + *%ipuz-yn%i, *%ipuz%i- is easily identified as
            <mentioned xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*pu</w><gloss><q>inflate
            (oneself)</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ine"><w/><gloss><q>make (become)
                    swollen</q></gloss></mentioned>, etc. with augmented -%ig%i(→%iz%i); cf.
            <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>pūga-</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><w>puñja-</w><gloss><q>mass</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                ><lang/><w>puzo</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ru"><w>puzyr'</w></mentioned>, ,
            <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>πυγή</w></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Walde—Pok."/><biblScope>II 79—81</biblScope></bibl>). The fact that
        %ip%i has not turned into %if(v)%i, despite the sound law, should be explained by the
        typical “expressivity” of the labial consonants %ip%i, %ib%i for the notions of “inflation”,
        “swelling”, compared to fricatives. Unusual is the identical vowel in Iron and Digor: %iu%i
        | %iu%i, instead of expected %iy%i | %iu%i or %iu%i | %iо%i.%r1%r The Ossetic word might
        also be connected to <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/><w>buzva</w></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ka"><w>abuzva</w><gloss><q>hunch (v.)</q></gloss></mentioned>, .</etym>
